org.vngx.jsch.algorithm

Class DefaultAlgorithmFactory<T extends Algorithm>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.vngx.jsch.algorithm.DefaultAlgorithmFactory<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of algorithm
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlgorithmFactory<T>

    public class DefaultAlgorithmFactory<T extends Algorithm>
extends Object
implements AlgorithmFactory<T>

    Default implementation of the AlgorithmFactory factory pattern which supports the use of generics to create instances of Algorithm of the specified type T. Instances store a map containing algorithm names mapped to their respective implementation Class, which is used to create new instances through reflection to the default no-arg constructor. The implementation caches requests to the isSupported method for additional performance.

    Note: Algorithm implementations MUST have a default empty constructor in order to be supported by this factory.

    Note: This implementation is thread-safe.

    Author:
    Michael Laudati
    See Also:
    Algorithm, AlgorithmFactory
